## Key Files
- `bridge/claude_desktop_edamame_mcp.mjs` - MCP bridge entry point
- `service/claude_desktop_extrapolator.mjs` - Transcript-to-model translation and push
- `adapters/session_prediction_adapter.mjs` - Transcript-to-payload conversion
- `service/config.mjs` - Configuration management
- E2E tests live in `../agent_security/tests/e2e/` -- run triggers with `--agent-type claude_desktop` (see `E2E_TESTS.md` there)

## How It Works
1. Claude Desktop produces session transcripts.
2. This package parses transcripts and forwards them to EDAMAME via MCP.
3. EDAMAME evaluates behavioral intent against live system telemetry.
4. Divergence verdicts surface through the control center or health checks.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- EDAMAME Security running on the same machine (app on macOS/Windows,
  `edamame_posture` CLI on Linux)

## Build & Test
